Class AbstractQueryAccessTypesByUriPattern

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.sql.AbstractQueryAccessTypesByUriPattern
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dao.query.IParameterizedQuerySql<IAccessType,IUriPattern>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    QueryAccessTypesByUriPattern

    public abstract class AbstractQueryAccessTypesByUriPattern
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.poesys.db.dao.query.IParameterizedQuerySql<IAccessType,IUriPattern>

    A query Command pattern object that implements a SQL query of a collection of AccessType objects using the primary key of an associated UriPattern object through the association AccessTypes using the association class AccessRule. This association is a many-to-many association from AccessType to UriPattern.

    This SQL specification contains a SQL statement that queries a collection of AccessType objects from the database table AccessType by joining to the database table AccessRule and using the primary key from UriPattern to query the collection.

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
